<div class="printable-area">
  <div class="container-fluid">
    <h2 class="normal custom-h2">Adding new content to Featured Workshops</h2>
    <p class='lead'>
      To add new content in the Featured Workshops section (figure 1), go to the CMS
      Dashboard – Workshops – Add New (figure 2). Be sure to select the “featured” check box,
      found above the “Objective” field.
    </p>

    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-6">
        <h4 class="normal">figure 1</h4>
        <a href="/images/help/featured-workshop-dashboard.png" target="_blank">
          <img src="/images/help/featured-workshop-dashboard.png" class="img-responsive" ></img></a>
        <br/>
        <h4 class="normal">figure 2</h4>
        <a href="/images/help/adding-a-featured-workshop-cms.png" target="_blank">
          <img src="/images/help/adding-a-featured-workshop-cms.png" class="img-responsive"></img></a>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-6"></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<hr />

<div class="printable-area">
  <div class="container-fluid">
    <h2 class="normal custom-h2">Editing content in Featured Workshops</h2>
    <p class='lead'>
      To edit information within this section, go to the CMS Dashboard – Workshops section and search
      for the item by name using the search field. Type the first word of the workshop name (Figure 1)
      then click on the pencil icon next to the workshop you’d like to edit. You will be redirected to
      the “Edit Workshop” page where you can make updates. (Figure 2)
      Save all changes by selecting the Save button at the bottom of the page. (Figure 3)
    </p>

    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-6">
        <h4 class="normal">figure 1</h4>
        <a href="/images/help/find-workshop-dashboard.png" target="_blank">
